Unzip - ( ftp://ftp.info-zip.org/pub/infozip/src/unzip60.zip )
  need at least version 6.0 ( defaul CentOS 5.5 si version 5.52 - can't open newer files ).
	wget ftp://ftp.info-zip.org/pub/infozip/src/unzip60.zip
	unzip unzip60.zip
	cd unzip60
	cp unix/Makefile .
	make generic
	sudo cp unzip funzip /usr/local/bin

BEDTools ( http://code.google.com/p/bedtools/ ) -
	messy installation
	download list:
		http://code.google.com/p/bedtools/downloads/list
	Direct Download:
		http://bedtools.googlecode.com/files/BEDTools.v2.15.0.tar.gz

	Directory name is not the same as the tarball name.
	make
	then manual copy to /usr/local/bin

Perl ( http://www.cpan.org/src/README.html )

	wget http://www.cpan.org/src/5.0/perl-5.14.2.tar.gz
	tar -xzf perl-5.14.2.tar.gz 
	cd perl-5.14.2
	./Configure -Dusethreads -des -Dprefix=/opt/perl-5.14.2
	make
	make install

	## Issues:
	##  1. "./Configure" instead of "./configure"
	##  2. custom parameters ( "-Dprefix" instead of "--prefix" )
	##  3. install to a custom location (not "/usr/local", to avoid messing up with the system)
	##  4. need to create symlinks from:
	##           /opt/perl-5.14.2/bin/*
	##       to
	##           /usr/local/bin
	##     $ for i in /opt/perl-5.14.2/bin/* ; do sudo ln -s $i /usr/local/bin/ ; done

	## NOTE:
	##   if re-running "./Configure" - old values are sometimes retained. best to delete the source directory and start fresh.
